# GUI — integration account filter

## Where it applies

Only **modules that consume provider integration data** use integration account filtering in the UI. The canonical list is the whitelist in `config/moduleIntegration.ts` (`mail`, `calendar`, `tasks`, `people`, `meetings`).

Do **not** add integration account filter UI to Organizer-only modules (dashboard, behaviors, teams, projects, coaching, statistics, network, feedback, etc.) unless product docs and `moduleIntegration.ts` are updated first.

## UI

- Use `components/integrations/ModuleIntegrationAccountFilter.vue` (mail-style list via `components/integrations/ProviderAccountsCard.vue`).
- Do **not** duplicate integration account selection inside `components/common/FilterContainer.vue` or ad hoc chip rows on those modules.
- Labels use shared i18n keys (e.g. `common.integrationAccounts`), not hard-coded strings.

## Data

- Account lists and predicates come from `composables/useModuleIntegrationAccounts.ts` and `utils/filterIntegrationAccountsByKind.ts`.
- When filtering rows by provider, use selected account ids together with `IntegrationAccount.id` / entity `providerAccountId` as today.
